Interface DefuzzificationFunction<T extends Number & Comparable<T>>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - numeric type used in this defuzzification function
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.function.BiFunction<NumericRange<T>,MembershipFunction<T>,Double>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BisectorDefuzzificationFunction, CentroidDefuzzificationFunction, LargestOfMaximaDefuzzificationFunction, MeanOfMaximaDefuzzificationFunction, SmallestOfMaximaDefuzzificationFunction

    public interface DefuzzificationFunction<T extends Number & Comparable<T>>
extends java.util.function.BiFunction<NumericRange<T>,MembershipFunction<T>,Double>
    A defuzzification function. Operates over the result of a membership function applied to a numeric range. Its output is always a crisp value.
    Since:
    0.2

    • Method Detail

      • apply

        Double apply(NumericRange<T> x,
             MembershipFunction<T> mf)
        Defuzzifies the result of a membership function applied to a numeric range.

        The range contains crisp values, that are transformed using the membership function. After the fuzzification, this method is called to obtain a crisp output.

        The crisp output depends on the chosen fuzzification and defuzzification functions.

        This method may throw different exceptions, depending on the implementation function.

        Specified by:
        apply in interface java.util.function.BiFunction<NumericRange<T extends Number & Comparable<T>>,MembershipFunction<T extends Number & Comparable<T>>,Double>

        x - numeric range
        mf - membership function applied to numeric range
        Returns:
        crisp result
